# ============================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================

# This file helps manage Claude Code's context window efficiently
# by excluding files that:
# 1. Are generated artifacts (build output, compiled files)
# 2. Are dependencies (node_modules, venv)
# 3. Contain secrets or credentials
# 4. Are large binary or data files
# 5. Are not relevant to code understanding

# Remember:
# - Be thoughtful about what you exclude
# - Don't exclude files you might need Claude to read or modify
# - You can always override by explicitly asking Claude to read an ignored file
# - Patterns work like .gitignore (supports *, ?, [abc], **)

# To verify what's being ignored:
# Use the Glob tool to see what files match patterns
